# ğŸª™ Crypto Buy/Sell/Hold Classifier
End-to-End Machine Learning System for Cryptocurrency Trading


# Project Overview

This capstone project builds a full Buy/Sell/Hold classifier for cryptocurrency markets using real historical data from the Binance API. The system performs data ingestion, feature engineering, label creation, model training, evaluation, backtesting, and model deployment.

The goal is to simulate a realistic machine learning workflow used in algorithmic trading and quantitative finance.

# Core Features
1. Real Market Data Fetching

Pulls OHLCV candlestick data from the Binance API.

Supports multiple intervals (1 minute, 1 hour, 1 day).

2. Data Cleaning & Preprocessing

Handles missing data, outliers, and type conversions.

Computes robust financial features:

RSI (14)

MACD (12/26/9)

SMA 

Bollinger Bands

Rolling volatility

Returns (1-day, 7-day)

3. Label Generation

Converts future price movements into:

Buy

Sell

Hold

Configurable thresholds allow fine-tuning signal sensitivity.

4. ML Model Training

Includes support for multiple classifiers:

Logistic Regression

Random Forest

Gradient Boosting

XGBoost

Lightgbm

Catboost

Includes:

Train/test/validation split

Feature scaling

Class balancing

Hyperparameter tuning

5. Evaluation & Backtesting

Uses precision, recall, F1-score, and accuracy.

Backtests predictions to simulate a trading strategy and compare returns to buy-and-hold.

6. Model Deployment

Serializes trained model using pickle/joblib.


